verses.text_plain: Now these be the last words of David. David the son of Jesse said, and the man who was raised up on high, the anointed of the God of Jacob, and the sweet psalmist of Israel, said,
verses.verse_html: 1Now these be the last words of David. David the son of Jesse said, and the man who was raised up on high, the anointed of the God of Jacob, and the sweet psalmist of Israel, said,

verses.text_plain: The Spirit of the Lord spake by me, and his word was in my tongue.
verses.verse_html: 2The Spirit of the Lord spake by me, and his word was in my tongue.

verses.text_plain: The God of Israel said, the Rock of Israel spake to me, He that ruleth over men must be just, ruling in the fear of God.
verses.verse_html:
3The God of Israel said, the Rock of Israel spake to me, He that ruleth over men must be just, ruling in the fear of God. ▼
▼ He…: or, Be thou ruler, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ He…: or, Be thou ruler, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ He…: or, Be thou ruler, etc

verses.text_plain: And he shall be as the light of the morning, when the sun riseth, even a morning without clouds; as the tender grass springing out of the earth by clear shining after rain.
verses.verse_html: 4And he shall be as the light of the morning, when the sun riseth, even a morning without clouds; as the tender grass springing out of the earth by clear shining after rain.

verses.text_plain: Although my house be not so with God; yet he hath made with me an everlasting covenant, ordered in all things, and sure: for this is all my salvation, and all my desire, although he make it not to grow.
verses.verse_html: 5Although my house be not so with God; yet he hath made with me an everlasting covenant, ordered in all things, and sure: for this is all my salvation, and all my desire, although he make it not to grow.

verses.text_plain: But the sons of Belial shall be all of them as thorns thrust away, because they cannot be taken with hands:
verses.verse_html: 6But the sons of Belial shall be all of them as thorns thrust away, because they cannot be taken with hands:

verses.text_plain: But the man that shall touch them must be fenced with iron and the staff of a spear; and they shall be utterly burned with fire in the same place.
verses.verse_html:
7But the man that shall touch them must be fenced with iron and the staff of a spear; and they shall be utterly burned with fire in the same place. ▼
▼ fenced: Heb. filled

verses.text_plain: These be the names of the mighty men whom David had: The Tachmonite that sat in the seat, chief among the captains; the same was Adino the Eznite: he lift up his spear against eight hundred, whom he slew at one time.
verses.verse_html:
8These be the names of the mighty men whom David had: The Tachmonite that sat in the seat, chief among the captains; the same was Adino the Eznite: he lift up his spear against eight hundred, whom he slew at one time. ▼
▼ The Tachmonite…: or, Joshebbassebet the Tachmonite, head of the three
 , ▼
▼ whom he…: Heb. slain
 , ▼
▼1ch 11:11 he lift…: from whom he…: Heb. slain

footnotes.body_text: ▼ The Tachmonite…: or, Joshebbassebet the Tachmonite, head of the three
footnotes.body_html: ▼ The Tachmonite…: or, Joshebbassebet the Tachmonite, head of the three
▼ whom he…: Heb. slain

footnotes.body_html: ▼1ch 11:11 he lift…: from whom he…: Heb. slain

verses.text_plain: And after him was Eleazar the son of Dodo the Ahohite, one of the three mighty men with David, when they defied the Philistines that were there gathered together to battle, and the men of Israel were gone away:
verses.verse_html: 9And after him was Eleazar the son of Dodo the Ahohite, one of the three mighty men with David, when they defied the Philistines that were there gathered together to battle, and the men of Israel were gone away:

verses.text_plain: He arose, and smote the Philistines until his hand was weary, and his hand clave unto the sword: and the Lord wrought a great victory that day; and the people returned after him only to spoil.
verses.verse_html: 10He arose, and smote the Philistines until his hand was weary, and his hand clave unto the sword: and the Lord wrought a great victory that day; and the people returned after him only to spoil.

verses.text_plain: And after him was Shammah the son of Agee the Hararite. And the Philistines were gathered together into a troop, where was a piece of ground full of lentiles: and the people fled from the Philistines.
verses.verse_html:
11And after him was Shammah the son of Agee the Hararite. And the Philistines were gathered together into a troop, where was a piece of ground full of lentiles: and the people fled from the Philistines. ▼
▼ into…: or, for foraging

footnotes.body_html: ▼ into…: or, for foraging

verses.text_plain: But he stood in the midst of the ground, and defended it, and slew the Philistines: and the Lord wrought a great victory.
verses.verse_html: 12But he stood in the midst of the ground, and defended it, and slew the Philistines: and the Lord wrought a great victory.

verses.text_plain: And three of the thirty chief went down, and came to David in the harvest time unto the cave of Adullam: and the troop of the Philistines pitched in the valley of Rephaim.
verses.verse_html:
13And three of the thirty chief went down, and came to David in the harvest time unto the cave of Adullam: and the troop of the Philistines pitched in the valley of Rephaim. ▼
▼ three…: or, the three captains over the thirty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ three…: or, the three captains over the thirty
footnotes.body_html: ▼ three…: or, the three captains over the thirty

verses.text_plain: And David was then in an hold, and the garrison of the Philistines was then in Beth–lehem.
verses.verse_html: 14And David was then in an hold, and the garrison of the Philistines was then in Beth–lehem.

verses.text_plain: And David longed, and said, Oh that one would give me drink of the water of the well of Beth–lehem, which is by the gate!
verses.verse_html: 15And David longed, and said, Oh that one would give me drink of the water of the well of Beth–lehem, which is by the gate!

tokens.text: Oh that one would give me drink

verses.text_plain: And the three mighty men brake through the host of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Beth–lehem, that was by the gate, and took it, and brought it to David: nevertheless he would not drink thereof, but poured it out unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16And the three mighty men brake through the host of the Philistines, and drew water out of the well of Beth–lehem, that was by the gate, and took it, and brought it to David: nevertheless he would not drink thereof, but poured it out unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And he said, Be it far from me, O Lord, that I should do this: is not this the blood of the men that went in jeopardy of their lives? therefore he would not drink it. These things did these three mighty men.
verses.verse_html: 17And he said, Be it far from me, O Lord, that I should do this: is not this the blood of the men that went in jeopardy of their lives? therefore he would not drink it. These things did these three mighty men.

verses.text_plain: And Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief among three. And he lifted up his spear against three hundred, and slew them, and had the name among three.
verses.verse_html:
18And Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief among three. And he lifted up his spear against three hundred, and slew them, and had the name among three. ▼
▼ and slew them: Heb. slain

footnotes.body_html: ▼ and slew them: Heb. slain

verses.text_plain: Was he not most honourable of three? therefore he was their captain: howbeit he attained not unto the first three.
verses.verse_html: 19Was he not most honourable of three? therefore he was their captain: howbeit he attained not unto the first three.

verses.text_plain: And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man, of Kabzeel, who had done many acts, he slew two lionlike men of Moab: he went down also and slew a lion in the midst of a pit in time of snow:
verses.verse_html:
20And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man, of Kabzeel, who had done many acts, he slew two lionlike men of Moab: he went down also and slew a lion in the midst of a pit in time of snow: ▼
▼ who…: Heb. great of acts
 , ▼
▼ lionlike…: Heb. lion of God

footnotes.body_html: ▼ who…: Heb. great of acts
▼ lionlike…: Heb. lion of God

verses.text_plain: And he slew an Egyptian, a goodly man: and the Egyptian had a spear in his hand; but he went down to him with a staff, and plucked the spear out of the Egyptian’s hand, and slew him with his own spear.
verses.verse_html:
21And he slew an Egyptian, a goodly man: and the Egyptian had a spear in his hand; but he went down to him with a staff, and plucked the spear out of the Egyptian’s hand, and slew him with his own spear. ▼
▼ a goodly…: Heb. a man of countenance, or, sight: also called, a man of great stature

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a goodly…: Heb. a man of countenance, or, sight: also called, a man of great stature
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a goodly…: Heb. a man of countenance, or, sight: also called, a man of great stature

verses.text_plain: These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and had the name among three mighty men.
verses.verse_html: 22These things did Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and had the name among three mighty men.

verses.text_plain: He was more honourable than the thirty, but he attained not to the first three. And David set him over his guard.
verses.verse_html:
23He was more honourable than the thirty, but he attained not to the first three. And David set him over his guard. ▼
▼ more…: or, honourable among the thirty
 , ▼
▼ guard: or, council: Heb. at his command

footnotes.body_html: ▼ guard: or, council: Heb. at his command

verses.text_plain: Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; Elhanan the son of Dodo of Beth–lehem,
verses.verse_html: 24Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; Elhanan the son of Dodo of Beth–lehem,

verses.text_plain: Shammah the Harodite, Elika the Harodite,
verses.verse_html: 25Shammah the Harodite, Elika the Harodite,

verses.text_plain: Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite,
verses.verse_html: 26Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite,

verses.text_plain: Abiezer the Anethothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite,
verses.verse_html: 27Abiezer the Anethothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite,

verses.text_plain: Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite,
verses.verse_html: 28Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite,

verses.text_plain: Heleb the son of Baanah, a Netophathite, Ittai the son of Ribai out of Gibeah of the children of Benjamin,
verses.verse_html: 29Heleb the son of Baanah, a Netophathite, Ittai the son of Ribai out of Gibeah of the children of Benjamin,

verses.text_plain: Benaiah the Pirathonite, Hiddai of the brooks of Gaash,
verses.verse_html:
30Benaiah the Pirathonite, Hiddai of the brooks of Gaash, ▼
▼ brooks: or, valleys

verses.text_plain: Abi–albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite,
verses.verse_html: 31Abi–albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite,

verses.text_plain: Eliahba the Shaalbonite, of the sons of Jashen, Jonathan,
verses.verse_html: 32Eliahba the Shaalbonite, of the sons of Jashen, Jonathan,

verses.text_plain: Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Hararite,
verses.verse_html: 33Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Hararite,

verses.text_plain: Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai, the son of the Maachathite, Eliam the son of Ahithophel the Gilonite,
verses.verse_html: 34Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai, the son of the Maachathite, Eliam the son of Ahithophel the Gilonite,

verses.text_plain: Hezrai the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite,
verses.verse_html: 35Hezrai the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite,

verses.text_plain: Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite,
verses.verse_html: 36Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite,

verses.text_plain: Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite, armourbearer to Joab the son of Zeruiah,
verses.verse_html: 37Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite, armourbearer to Joab the son of Zeruiah,

verses.text_plain: Ira an Ithrite, Gareb an Ithrite,
verses.verse_html: 38Ira an Ithrite, Gareb an Ithrite,

verses.text_plain: Uriah the Hittite: thirty and seven in all.
verses.verse_html: 39Uriah the Hittite: thirty and seven in all.
